Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Trim, peel, and cut @carrots{12%ounce} on a diagonal into ½-inch-thick pieces (halve lengthwise first if carrots are on the larger side). Cut @cauliflower florets{10%ounce} into bite-size pieces. Peel and mince or grate @garlic{2%clove}; reserve a pinch in a #small bowl{} (you'll use it in Step 5).

Toss carrots and cauliflower on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @cooking oil{4%teaspoon}, @Tunisian spice blend{1%tablespoon}, a big pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Roast on top rack until browned and tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of oil in a #small pot{} over medium-high heat. Add remaining garlic; cook, stirring, until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Stir in @basmati rice{1/2%cup}, 3/4 cup water (1 1/2 cups for 4 servings), @veggie stock concentrate{1}, and a pinch of salt. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

While rice cooks, mince @cilantro{1/4%ounce}. Zest and quarter @lemon{1}. Mince @jalapeño{1}, removing ribs and seeds for less heat.

== Chermoula ==

To #bowl{} with reserved garlic, add cilantro, 2 TBSP @olive oil{4%teaspoon}, salt, and pepper. Add a squeeze of lemon juice and as much jalapeño as you like. Set chermoula aside.

In a second small bowl, whisk together @tahini{2%tablespoon}, juice from half a lemon, 1 TBSP olive oil, and @sugar{1/4%teaspoon} (for 4, use juice from a whole lemon, 2 TBSP olive oil, and ½ tsp sugar). Add water 1 TBSP at a time until sauce reaches a drizzling consistency. Season tahini sauce with salt and pepper.

> Tahini will thicken at first as you add water but will then thin out again. We used 2 TBSP water for 2 servings, 3 TBSP for 4 servings.

== Charred Tomatoes ==

Heat a drizzle of oil in a #large pan{} over high heat. Add @grape tomatoes{4%ounce} and cook, undisturbed, until lightly charred, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Stir tomatoes; cook, stirring occasionally, until tender, ~{1-2%minutes} more. Season with salt and pepper.

== Assembly ==

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in half the lemon zest and a drizzle of @olive oil{}. Season with salt and pepper.

Divide rice between #bowls{}; top with roasted veggies and charred tomatoes. Drizzle with chermoula and tahini sauce.

Garnish with @almonds{1/2%ounce} and remaining lemon zest. Serve with any remaining lemon wedges on the side.